The paper discusses a theory of induction and belief change, which are topics that are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on epistemology and probability theory suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. The paper also touches on information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR), which are related to belief change and probability. Finally, the paper briefly compares its theory with other logical frameworks, which could place it in the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
